      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i need some help with these two interview transcripts for a customer service position. can u summarize how well each person communicates their ideas and if they seem like they'd fit in a professional office setting? here they are:\n\nCandidate A:\nInterviewer: How do you handle a frustrated customer?\nCandidate A: When a customer is upset, I make sure to listen to their entire concern without interrupting them. I find that letting them vent helps de-escalate the situation. After that, I acknowledge their feelings and work as quickly as possible to find a solution that aligns with our company policy. It's important to stay calm and professional throughout the process.\n\nCandidate B:\nInterviewer: How do you handle a frustrated customer?\nCandidate B: When a customer get mad, i make sure i'm listenin to what they sayin without interruptin. i find dat lettin them vent help de-escalate the situation. After dat, i acknowledge how they feelin and work as fast as i can to find a solution dat fit with the company policy. It's important to stay calm and professional through the whole thing.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
